text: Uh-Oh, maybe these teeth can be repaired.
Why do I keep touching this?
Are you Brandon, grandson of Kallak?
We are of the Other Kingdom, Brandon.
Why would the Land speak to me?
Magic spells of an evil intent...
After all, you are a talking tree.
Can't you use your power to fight this evil?
Evil exists only in the Kingdom of Man, Brandon.
The magic Kyragem, symbol of the pact...
Now, it can no longer protect us.
You, Brandon, must oppose on our behalf.
Your destiny was forged before your birth.
But I wouldn't know where to start.
Let your faith guide you, Brandon.
I thought my sandals were in here.
I think there's already something in there.
I can see plenty of dead trees from here.
I'll have to go get her.
Should I lay Grandfather on the bed?
I don't think there's any way to move him.
I don't want to carry this around!
I don't think he can chew.
Perhaps my magic can heal Grandfather...
